         The
          Configuration Analyst, Team Lead
         , provides direction to the Health and Welfare Configuration Analyst on assigned clients, including ongoing system integrity and stability, and system configuration changes. Provides hands-on advice and direction to CAs on complex issues. Functions as a product and technical expert for team members, clients, sales, and development. Conducts periodic system audits to ensure that system configuration is consistent with client requirements. Transitions new clients from Implementation to Operations. Ensures that operational and procedural standards for CAs are identified and that compliance monitoring occurs for assigned clients. Interfaces with internal and external clients to resolve escalated issues and answer product and process questions. Makes complex configuration changes to the application and resolves escalated issues for multiple custom client databases. This position will play an active role in the interviewing, training and mentoring of new CA associates and providing feedback to management to ensure proper training, performance management and project/client assignment recommendations for new associate(s) as well as other CA associates on the team. Additional responsibilities include; researching new features and functionality and sharing this knowledge with the CAs through training, documentation and conference calls. Will also be required to act as project lead for resolution of global issues, application upgrades or other business unit initiatives. Participates in client meetings and/or conference calls as needed.
